<title type="html"><![CDATA[Most advanced nes game with out a chip/mapper?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7299&amp;p=71723#p71723"><![CDATA[
All of them use lots of ticks and such, as for the most advanced, can't really tell unless you disassemble every game and grade them on "Quality of Code."<br /><br /><br />And plus some mappers don't do anything extra, they just add more space. MMC3 has scanline, so that'd probably not count here, but do want MMC1 to count?<br /><br />As for no chips, I think the combo carts SMB/DH and SMB/WCTM/DH would win since they're the only ones without chips. And then there's the Gyromite with the converter without actual "chips." Haha.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4311">3gengames</a> — Tue Dec 21, 2010 2:39 pm</p><hr />
